WEBVTT

00:01.877 --> 00:03.378
Dinner out ‐‐
this is new.

00:03.378 --> 00:04.796
Oh, my darlings like to splurge
once in a while.

00:04.796 --> 00:07.132
Kids' menu, kids' menu,
kids' menu.

00:07.132 --> 00:08.759
Yeah, but this is
for 12 and under.

00:08.759 --> 00:10.552
Which they all are.

00:10.552 --> 00:11.887
12, 10, 8.

00:11.887 --> 00:14.139
Mommy, they didn't
bring me crayons!

00:14.139 --> 00:15.349
God, I love you.

00:15.349 --> 00:17.142
You think
you can pull off 12?

00:17.142 --> 00:21.813
"CP don't" ‐‐
if you want to say

00:21.813 --> 00:23.565
"cerebral palsy don't crack,"
<i>you</i> say it.

00:23.565 --> 00:25.484
[ Laughs ]

00:25.484 --> 00:26.276
Maya.

00:26.276 --> 00:27.736
[ Gasps ]

00:27.736 --> 00:28.779
God, it's happening.

00:28.779 --> 00:30.113
He's coming this way.
Does he see us?

00:30.113 --> 00:31.323
The management?

00:31.323 --> 00:33.283
We're too old
for these menus.

00:33.283 --> 00:35.118
I knew I should've shaved
before we came.

00:35.118 --> 00:36.328
Tell me when it's over.

00:36.328 --> 00:38.747
♪ La, la, la, la, la ♪
Hi, Maya.

00:38.747 --> 00:39.581
Jimmy.

00:39.581 --> 00:41.041
Hey, Ethan.

00:41.041 --> 00:42.751
You look great
from down here.

00:42.751 --> 00:43.919
Oh, look at that.

00:43.919 --> 00:45.712
We thought it'd be weird
if we saw you again.

00:45.712 --> 00:46.713
Who is this guy?

00:46.713 --> 00:48.298
Uh, kids, Kenneth,

00:48.298 --> 00:51.176
Ethan used to be
your father's roommate.

00:51.176 --> 00:54.012
Until he stole
my fiancée...

00:54.012 --> 00:55.889
who's sitting
right there.

00:55.889 --> 00:56.640
What?

00:56.640 --> 00:57.933
Wha...?

00:58.767 --> 01:00.769
I can't take it
anymore!

01:00.769 --> 01:03.230
I'm 14.
I'm sorry!

01:07.442 --> 01:12.197
Ray and Dylan: Tell us! Tell us!
Tell us! Tell us! Tell us!

01:12.197 --> 01:13.407
Dad,
it's not enough pressure.

01:13.407 --> 01:15.993
We need you to cover JJ.
Tell us! Tell us! Tell us!

01:15.993 --> 01:17.244
Tell us! Tell us! Tell us!

01:17.244 --> 01:19.496
Okay, okay, quickly.

01:19.496 --> 01:21.331
I used to date Ethan,
and then we got engaged,

01:21.331 --> 01:23.083
even though we weren't
right for each other.

01:23.083 --> 01:24.501
I mean,
among other things,

01:24.501 --> 01:27.212
he always insisted that
we were on time for everything.

01:27.212 --> 01:28.797
Is he my real dad?

01:28.797 --> 01:30.591
I always found myself
having much more fun

01:30.591 --> 01:32.551
when I was hanging out
at Ethan's apartment ‐‐

01:32.551 --> 01:35.804
when I was there
with his roommate, Jimmy.

01:35.804 --> 01:39.349
One evening ‐‐ it
was Valentine's Day,
as a matter of fact ‐‐

01:39.349 --> 01:42.185
I took your mom out for a drink,
professed my love to her,

01:42.185 --> 01:44.062
she admitted
she felt the same way,

01:44.062 --> 01:46.815
and it was the happiest moment
of my life.

01:46.815 --> 01:47.816
And then Ethan showed up.

01:47.816 --> 01:49.401
There were words,
and a punch ‐‐

01:49.401 --> 01:51.153
quite a punch,
as a matter of fact.

01:51.153 --> 01:53.238
Ethan punched Dad?
No, no.

01:53.238 --> 01:54.197
Ethan was the one
who got punched.

01:54.197 --> 01:56.491
"Who punched Ethan?
Mom?"

01:56.491 --> 01:58.577
Mom punched Ethan
because he beat up Dad?

01:58.577 --> 01:59.786
<i>I</i> punched Ethan.

01:59.786 --> 02:01.246
I can punch people, too.

02:01.246 --> 02:03.081
Your dad socked him <i>good.</i>

02:03.081 --> 02:05.542
Pow.
Very hot.

02:05.542 --> 02:06.668
Violence is bad.

02:06.668 --> 02:07.711
An illicit love?

02:07.711 --> 02:09.129
Romantic fisticuffs?

02:09.129 --> 02:10.297
Oh, my!

02:10.297 --> 02:11.923
Don't talk like
a British dowager, darling.

02:11.923 --> 02:13.842
Then don't titillate me
like her naughty niece.

02:13.842 --> 02:15.927
Let me translate ‐‐
you guys brang the heat.

02:15.927 --> 02:17.346
Yeah.
Where did it go?

02:17.346 --> 02:18.305
Oi!

02:18.305 --> 02:20.098
We are still
brang‐ing it.

02:20.098 --> 02:21.391
You guys just don't
see us that way

02:21.391 --> 02:22.476
because we're your parents.

02:22.476 --> 02:23.435
Yeah,
I don't think that's it.

02:23.435 --> 02:24.770
I can picture
Grandma and Grandpa.

02:24.770 --> 02:26.313
"Yeah. Hot‐cha."

02:26.313 --> 02:29.941
I will have you know,
we are still very hot‐cha.

02:29.941 --> 02:31.985
Hot‐ <i>cha.</i>

02:31.985 --> 02:34.738
I'm sorry, are you seriously
demonstrating the heat right now

02:34.738 --> 02:35.530
by holding hands?

02:35.530 --> 02:36.740
Hotly.

02:36.740 --> 02:37.908
Nobody tell Ethan.

02:37.908 --> 02:38.950
He's gonna hit Dad again.

02:38.950 --> 02:40.077
I hit <i>him!</i>

02:40.827 --> 02:42.954
Candygram.

02:42.954 --> 02:45.040
[ Scoffs ] You know
you guys are already weird.

02:45.040 --> 02:46.291
You don't need
to lean into it.

02:47.292 --> 02:48.752
"I'm Cupid."

02:48.752 --> 02:50.253
And I'm Cupid's enforcer,

02:50.253 --> 02:52.714
'cause love
is sometimes dangerous.

02:52.714 --> 02:56.510
JJ volunteered to deliver all
the Valentine's Day candygrams

02:56.510 --> 02:57.511
for the school fundraiser.

02:57.511 --> 02:58.553
Bad idea.

02:58.553 --> 03:00.013
JJ can't be around
all this candy.

03:00.013 --> 03:02.099
Why?
Is this a CP thing?

03:02.099 --> 03:04.643
No, it's
a "JJ's disgusting" thing.

03:04.643 --> 03:05.727
He's an addict.

03:05.727 --> 03:07.145
JJ, is this true?

03:09.147 --> 03:11.358
[ Snorts ]
I think we'll be fine.

03:11.358 --> 03:14.778
Remember,
you chose this.

03:14.778 --> 03:17.531
I don't understand
this whole candygram thing.

03:17.531 --> 03:19.700
Nothing says romance
like a cheap box of sugar.

03:21.576 --> 03:22.661
Candygram.

03:22.661 --> 03:24.246
Love is real!

03:24.246 --> 03:26.039
Who would send Ray
a candygram?

03:26.039 --> 03:27.541
"Secret admirer."

03:27.541 --> 03:29.167
Yeah,
I'm not buying it.

03:29.167 --> 03:32.712
I was once like you ‐‐
candygram‐less.

03:32.712 --> 03:34.548
It gets better.

03:35.924 --> 03:37.759
Give me that list.

03:37.759 --> 03:39.594
Hey.

03:39.594 --> 03:41.221
Why do you like
Ray DiMeo?

03:41.221 --> 03:42.722
Who wouldn't like
Ray DiMeo?

03:42.722 --> 03:45.308
Look at him.

03:45.308 --> 03:46.935
Oh.

03:46.935 --> 03:48.937
Yeah,
that's Ray <i>DeBlasio.</i>

03:48.937 --> 03:50.772
Oh.
I'm new here.

03:50.772 --> 03:52.524
Um, who's Ray DiMeo?

03:52.524 --> 03:53.942
[ Chuckles ]

03:53.942 --> 03:55.485
Someone who's about
to get messed with.

03:57.028 --> 03:58.613
Hey,
should we be worried

03:58.613 --> 04:01.032
that the kids don't
see us as romantic?

04:01.032 --> 04:04.035
I've been
powering through.

04:04.035 --> 04:05.912
[ Sighs ] Who cares
what they think?

04:05.912 --> 04:07.456
It's about
what we think.

04:07.456 --> 04:10.750
Okay, do <i>we</i> think we're as hot
as we used to be?

04:10.750 --> 04:12.252
Who cares
what we think?

04:12.252 --> 04:13.044
Jimmy!

04:13.044 --> 04:14.129
It works.

04:14.129 --> 04:15.797
<i>We</i> work.

04:15.797 --> 04:17.591
It's deeper, richer.

04:17.591 --> 04:19.426
Do you need me to tell you
the divorce statistics

04:19.426 --> 04:20.635
for special‐needs
families?

04:20.635 --> 04:22.804
If you want to get something
going, you should.

04:24.514 --> 04:25.682
Seven.

04:25.682 --> 04:27.517
Oh, hey, guys.

04:27.517 --> 04:29.561
Yeah, a lot of people
get into relationships

04:29.561 --> 04:30.437
and it all goes to hell.

04:30.437 --> 04:31.480
I want to keep it tight.

04:31.480 --> 04:33.273
Kenneth: Oh, well,
be careful, now.

04:33.273 --> 04:35.192
Still want to look like
the guy she fell in love with.

04:35.192 --> 04:37.861
Good point.
I'm gonna hit the showers.

04:37.861 --> 04:39.988
Keep him away
from my candy.

04:39.988 --> 04:42.115
Dude,
where's the trust?

04:42.115 --> 04:44.451
Ooh, I got to go.

04:44.451 --> 04:47.537
[ Scoffs ] I can leave you
with this, right?

04:47.537 --> 04:48.455
Yeah.

04:52.793 --> 04:56.379
[ Door creaks ]

04:56.379 --> 04:57.964
Jimmy,
we've got to be careful.

04:57.964 --> 04:59.674
If we take each other
for granted,

04:59.674 --> 05:02.594
one day we're gonna wake up
and we're gonna be roommates.

05:02.594 --> 05:04.346
Dylan.
What?

05:04.346 --> 05:06.097
I just need Dad to change
the parental settings

05:06.097 --> 05:08.099
so I can create a fake account
and catfish Ray.

05:08.099 --> 05:09.518
Well, that's fine,
but you can't just

05:09.518 --> 05:11.019
walk in here
without knocking.

05:11.019 --> 05:12.354
<i>Is</i> that fine?

05:12.354 --> 05:13.647
Were you
not at all concerned

05:13.647 --> 05:15.232
about what you might
be walking into?

05:15.232 --> 05:16.358
Like that
Dad ripped one?

05:16.358 --> 05:18.485
[ Sighs ]
To be honest,
I really was,

05:18.485 --> 05:20.070
but I can't be ruled
by fear.

05:22.823 --> 05:24.991
[ Door closes ]
See that ‐‐
kids burst in,

05:24.991 --> 05:27.077
assuming
nothing is happening.

05:27.077 --> 05:28.662
Right ‐‐ enough.

05:28.662 --> 05:29.830
I'm done.
I'm gonna fix this.

05:29.830 --> 05:30.997
It's Valentine's Day
coming.

05:30.997 --> 05:32.123
We don't do
Valentine's Day.

05:32.123 --> 05:33.750
This year, we do.

05:33.750 --> 05:35.001
It's the night that
you declared your love for me

05:35.001 --> 05:36.378
and fought for me.

05:36.378 --> 05:38.046
And this year,
it's gonna be the night

05:38.046 --> 05:39.130
that we get
our heat back.

05:39.130 --> 05:40.382
All right.
All right.

05:40.382 --> 05:43.510
So you want to celebrate
this bogus Hallmark holiday?

05:43.510 --> 05:44.678
You know I do, baby.

05:44.678 --> 05:46.096
What kind of presents
you want?

05:46.096 --> 05:47.180
You want
thoughtful presents?

05:47.180 --> 05:48.515
I want
thoughtful presents

05:48.515 --> 05:51.017
that also manage
to be somehow practical.

05:51.017 --> 05:52.269
Yeah,
and I want a card.

05:52.269 --> 05:53.061
Yeah, you want a card.

05:53.061 --> 05:54.271
I'm gonna get you
one of those cards

05:54.271 --> 05:55.689
that plays a song
when you open it up.

05:55.689 --> 05:56.940
Go on.

05:56.940 --> 05:57.941
Are we on?

05:57.941 --> 05:59.234
Yeah, we're on.

06:01.486 --> 06:03.029
Ugh,
I don't want to see that.

06:03.029 --> 06:04.489
Yeah, no, that's right.
Spread the word.

06:08.618 --> 06:11.121
Hey, Ray, I know
you're waiting to hear

06:11.121 --> 06:12.873
from your
secret admirer.

06:12.873 --> 06:14.583
Maybe you should
check your phone?

06:14.583 --> 06:16.418
I would,
but I'm on a digital diet.

06:16.418 --> 06:17.711
Recent studies show

06:17.711 --> 06:19.129
that screen time before bed
can affect ‐‐

06:19.129 --> 06:21.006
Oh, my gosh.
She texted you.

06:21.006 --> 06:23.091
Give me.

06:23.091 --> 06:26.678
Girl: <i>Hi, Ray,</i>
<i>it's your secret admirer.</i>

06:26.678 --> 06:27.804
<i>Hi, secret admirer.</i>

06:27.804 --> 06:29.431
<i>Thanks for the candies.</i>

06:29.431 --> 06:30.640
<i>Who are you?</i>

06:30.640 --> 06:32.434
<i>My name's Fiona.</i>
<i>I go to Eastlake.</i>

06:32.434 --> 06:34.269
<i>I saw you</i>
<i>at the basketball game.</i>

06:34.269 --> 06:35.937
<i>Do you have</i>
<i>a girlfriend?</i>

06:35.937 --> 06:38.356
<i>I'm currently</i>
<i>between girlfriends.</i>

06:38.356 --> 06:40.692
<i>I've received</i>
<i>a number of candygrams,</i>

06:40.692 --> 06:42.319
<i>but yours</i>
<i>really stood out.</i>

06:42.319 --> 06:44.112
<i>So, what do you</i>
<i>look like?</i>

06:44.112 --> 06:47.240
<i>A lot of people tell me I look</i>
<i>like Emma Watson but trashier.</i>

06:47.240 --> 06:50.327
[ Quietly ]
Yes, yes, yes.

06:50.327 --> 06:52.370
<i>Would you like to be exclusive</i>
<i>forever, starting now?</i>

06:52.370 --> 06:54.623
<i>Oh, Ray, I thought</i>
<i>you'd never ask.</i>

06:54.623 --> 06:56.124
<i>Can we meet soon?</i>

06:56.124 --> 06:58.001
<i>I would invite you to</i>
<i>my school's Valentine's dance,</i>

06:58.001 --> 07:00.879
<i>but I've been banned because</i>
<i>my dancing is too passionate.</i>

07:00.879 --> 07:03.590
<i>Then I insist</i>
<i>you join me</i>

07:03.590 --> 07:05.091
<i>at my school's</i>
<i>Valentine's Day dance.</i>

07:05.091 --> 07:06.593
<i>It's a date.</i>

07:06.593 --> 07:08.553
<i>Do you have any requests</i>
<i>for when I meet you?</i>

07:08.553 --> 07:10.555
<i>You're perfect</i>
<i>just the way you are.</i>

07:10.555 --> 07:11.514
<i>Any for me?</i>

07:11.514 --> 07:13.350
<i>Thanks for asking.</i>

07:13.350 --> 07:15.977
<i>Please wear</i>
<i>platform heels, a cape,</i>

07:15.977 --> 07:17.937
<i>those baggy half‐pants</i>
<i>old‐timey directors wear ‐‐</i>

07:17.937 --> 07:20.732
Dylan,
do we have any jodhpurs?

07:20.732 --> 07:23.652
Good morning, my love.

07:23.652 --> 07:25.362
What?

07:25.362 --> 07:27.405
Uh,
did I miss something?

07:27.405 --> 07:28.865
Is it already
Valentine's Day?

07:28.865 --> 07:30.283
This is just a preview.
Oh.

07:30.283 --> 07:32.702
My actual gift
is way better.

07:32.702 --> 07:35.288
Oh, so, you ‐‐ you've already
planned something, have you?

07:35.288 --> 07:36.081
Like I have.

07:36.081 --> 07:38.500
This was a great idea.

07:38.500 --> 07:40.001
I‐I can't wait to see
what you have in store.

07:40.001 --> 07:42.212
Oh, and each one

07:42.212 --> 07:43.838
has a reason I love you
written on it.

07:43.838 --> 07:45.048
Each what?

07:47.717 --> 07:50.553
Aw,
this was a bad idea.

07:50.553 --> 07:52.097
I've got nothing.

07:52.097 --> 07:55.016
There aren't this many reasons
to love me!

07:57.977 --> 08:02.440
Is it possible there's
no correct angle for an
adult man to wear a halo?

08:09.364 --> 08:13.118
♪♪

08:15.370 --> 08:17.288
Kenneth:
What did you...

08:20.625 --> 08:23.712
"Don't look at me."

08:26.548 --> 08:29.634
<i>♪ It's hard to say, but</i>
<i>you know that you've found it ♪</i>
Maya: Oh, Jimmy.

08:29.634 --> 08:31.928
<i>♪ You didn't know that it's...♪</i>
I am so screwed.

08:31.928 --> 08:33.471
Dylan:
Saw his video, huh?

08:33.471 --> 08:34.764
Yeah.

08:34.764 --> 08:35.890
If you didn't marry Dad,
I would.

08:35.890 --> 08:38.184
[ Keyboard clacks, music stops ]
I have no idea
what to do for him.

08:38.184 --> 08:39.853
Nothing could be
as good as this.

08:39.853 --> 08:42.814
Well, us DiMeo men are gifted
in matters of the heart.

08:42.814 --> 08:44.274
[ Chuckles ]

08:44.274 --> 08:46.151
Aw, darling, I needed that.
Thank you.

08:46.151 --> 08:48.653
You know, I might be able to
help you figure something out.

08:48.653 --> 08:50.739
Think back to when you and Dad
first got together.

08:50.739 --> 08:51.948
Dylan: Yeah,
what about the night

08:51.948 --> 08:53.533
you two declared your love
for each other?

08:53.533 --> 08:54.993
That sounded
pretty romantic.

08:54.993 --> 08:56.077
That is
a brilliant idea.

08:56.077 --> 08:57.495
I could re‐create
the night.

08:57.495 --> 08:58.955
Perfect.
Where did it happen?

08:58.955 --> 09:00.957
Some bar.
Your dad knows.

09:00.957 --> 09:02.250
What kind of music
was playing?

09:02.250 --> 09:03.501
I don't know.
Dad's the music guy.

09:03.501 --> 09:05.086
You really don't
remember any of it?

09:05.086 --> 09:06.588
You are
really bad at this.

09:06.588 --> 09:07.922
I know!

09:07.922 --> 09:10.467
Oh, my God,
and you're dad's amazing.

09:10.467 --> 09:13.762
You know,
there might be one person

09:13.762 --> 09:15.430
that can help re‐create
that night.

09:15.430 --> 09:16.222
Who?

09:16.222 --> 09:17.557
Oh.

09:17.557 --> 09:20.185
You want me to help <i>you?</i>
Really?

09:20.185 --> 09:21.478
Well, I know
it's a bit uncomfortable.

09:21.478 --> 09:22.771
Yeah.

09:22.771 --> 09:24.439
Look, don't think of it
so much as helping ‐‐

09:24.439 --> 09:27.442
uh, more of a chance
to be a know‐it‐all.

09:27.442 --> 09:29.110
You are still a know‐it‐all,
aren't you?

09:29.110 --> 09:30.612
Yeah,
I kind of am, yeah.

09:30.612 --> 09:34.407
Now, the night
that you found...

09:34.407 --> 09:37.035
Jimmy and me together ‐‐

09:37.035 --> 09:39.204
it was in a bar,
wasn't it?

09:39.204 --> 09:40.747
It wasn't our first of the
night ‐‐ it's a bit fuzzy.

09:40.747 --> 09:41.664
I don't care.

09:41.664 --> 09:42.999
Might you
remember the name?

09:42.999 --> 09:45.835
You do realize that the most
romantic night of your life

09:45.835 --> 09:48.630
happens also to be the most
humiliating night of mine?

09:48.630 --> 09:50.673
Awfully long name
for a bar.

09:50.673 --> 09:52.634
[ Chuckles ]
No?

09:52.634 --> 09:53.802
You ever dodge a bullet

09:53.802 --> 09:55.678
and then have coffee with it
18 years later?

09:55.678 --> 09:57.347
All right,
moving on, moving on.

09:57.347 --> 09:58.807
There was
a song playing.
There was.

09:58.807 --> 10:00.016
Do you remember
what it was?
I do.

10:00.016 --> 10:01.643
Are you gonna tell me?
Depends.

10:01.643 --> 10:03.978
On?
On whether or not
you dumped me 18 years ago.

10:03.978 --> 10:05.105
Ohh.

10:05.105 --> 10:06.564
Ooh.

10:06.564 --> 10:10.193
You still
have feelings for me.

10:10.193 --> 10:12.278
[ Laughs ]

10:12.278 --> 10:13.738
That's absurd.
[ Door bells jingle ]

10:13.738 --> 10:15.240
I'm happily married,
so...

10:15.240 --> 10:17.617
Ooh,
sorry I'm late, hon.
Oh. Hi.

10:17.617 --> 10:18.493
[ Smooch ]

10:18.493 --> 10:19.160
Traffic.

10:20.328 --> 10:21.788
‐What?
‐What?

10:21.788 --> 10:23.206
What?
That's your wife?

10:23.206 --> 10:26.000
Yes.
With the curly hair
and the being late?

10:26.000 --> 10:26.960
[ Imitating Allison ]
"Traffic."

10:26.960 --> 10:29.546
[ Groans ]
Bloody hell.

10:29.546 --> 10:30.421
Mm!

10:30.421 --> 10:32.006
Very sad, actually.

10:32.006 --> 10:33.967
I'm allowed
to have a type.

10:33.967 --> 10:36.469
How could you do this,
JJ?

10:36.469 --> 10:39.305
"I had a weak moment."

10:39.305 --> 10:43.643
Dude, you ate
17 boxes of chocolate

10:43.643 --> 10:44.644
in that closet.

10:44.644 --> 10:45.812
How'd you even
open up the boxes?

10:48.148 --> 10:52.443
"I see the chocolate, I wake up,
I don't see the choc‐‐"

10:52.443 --> 10:55.363
Okay, well, you know,
these weren't just chocolates.

10:55.363 --> 10:59.534
These were tokens of love
people trusted us with.

10:59.534 --> 11:01.870
What are you gonna
do about it?

11:01.870 --> 11:03.872
"Don't know.
Can't think.

11:03.872 --> 11:05.707
Need more chocolate."

11:05.707 --> 11:06.916
No more chocolate!

11:07.792 --> 11:09.377
What are you doing?

11:09.377 --> 11:12.088
Fiona wants to do a belly dance
at the school dance,

11:12.088 --> 11:13.506
so I'm loosening up
my hips.

11:13.506 --> 11:15.175
They're supposed
to tell a story.

11:15.175 --> 11:16.718
It's a fascinating
art form.

11:16.718 --> 11:18.344
[ Water running ]
I'm on dishes tonight.

11:18.344 --> 11:20.138
I'm doing them for you.
Why?

11:20.138 --> 11:22.307
Just spreading the love.

11:22.307 --> 11:23.474
My heart's so full of it
these days,

11:23.474 --> 11:24.726
why not pay it forward?

11:24.726 --> 11:27.520
But you ‐‐ you haven't even
met her yet.

11:27.520 --> 11:28.813
I know.

11:28.813 --> 11:30.190
I'm trying not
to get my hopes up,

11:30.190 --> 11:31.482
but guess what?

11:31.482 --> 11:32.942
They are up, baby.

11:32.942 --> 11:34.110
Or as my hips
would say...

11:36.779 --> 11:39.908
Oh, you're kidding me.

11:41.784 --> 11:44.913
"Wine enters,
blah, blah, blah.

11:44.913 --> 11:48.374
I look at you, I sigh.
Yeats."

11:48.374 --> 11:51.461
Oh, come on, wine!
We're friends!

11:51.461 --> 11:52.921
Come on.

11:52.921 --> 11:55.006
It's Valentine's Day,
it's not that hard.

11:55.006 --> 11:57.008
All I wanted to do
was to bring us closer.

11:57.008 --> 11:58.676
And now we're gonna
have to celebrate

11:58.676 --> 12:00.678
this stupid
bloody holiday.

12:00.678 --> 12:04.307
And Jimmy is gonna end up
feeling neglected and unloved.

12:06.017 --> 12:08.144
Ugh, sod it, there's only
one thing left for me to do.

12:08.144 --> 12:09.479
Come clean
and hope he understands.

12:09.479 --> 12:10.772
No.

12:10.772 --> 12:12.106
I got to blow up
Valentine's Day.

12:16.694 --> 12:18.446
[ School bell rings ]
Dr. Miller.
Um, I need your help.

12:18.446 --> 12:20.907
I got all worked up
about Valentine's Day ‐‐

12:20.907 --> 12:22.992
made a big stink
for absolutely no reason.

12:22.992 --> 12:24.160
You <i>do</i> do that.

12:24.160 --> 12:25.536
Anyway,
my plan didn't happen,

12:25.536 --> 12:26.913
and now I have
to pull a fire alarm

12:26.913 --> 12:27.997
on the whole holiday.

12:27.997 --> 12:29.499
You have to be
my excuse.

12:29.499 --> 12:31.960
Okay.

12:31.960 --> 12:34.587
But a time will come
when I will want a favor
from you in exchange.

12:34.587 --> 12:37.632
Mm, really?

12:37.632 --> 12:39.384
Nice power play,
Dr. Miller.

12:39.384 --> 12:41.552
Very well‐done.
Very proud of you, actually.

12:41.552 --> 12:42.637
Oh, that's favor enough.

12:42.637 --> 12:44.055
Call it even.
[ Chuckles ]

12:44.055 --> 12:46.182
Okay, man,
here's the plan.

12:46.182 --> 12:48.226
You're gonna replace
the candygrams you ate

12:48.226 --> 12:50.019
with candygrams
you receive.

12:50.019 --> 12:52.689
So get out there
and charm 17 people

12:52.689 --> 12:54.148
into sending you
candygrams.

12:54.148 --> 12:55.191
Got it?

12:55.191 --> 12:56.859
JJ likes your jeans.

12:56.859 --> 12:58.278
JJ likes your hair.

12:58.278 --> 12:59.696
[ Louder ]
JJ likes your hair!

12:59.696 --> 13:01.823
Now, who's this candygram
go to ‐‐ JJ?

13:01.823 --> 13:03.574
JJ.
JJ.

13:03.574 --> 13:07.078
Free cart rides, except
you got to buy a candygram.

13:07.078 --> 13:08.788
You're gonna buy
a candygram for JJ?

13:08.788 --> 13:10.498
Now, who's
this candygram going to?

13:10.498 --> 13:12.166
JJ?
JJ.

13:12.166 --> 13:15.044
JJ, you have
so many sweethearts.

13:15.044 --> 13:16.421
Give me that.

13:16.421 --> 13:17.463
Give me that.

13:17.463 --> 13:18.881
Hey,
what are you doing?

13:18.881 --> 13:20.341
Stop it!

13:20.341 --> 13:24.178
"It's very sweet
you're helping me."

13:25.596 --> 13:27.890
All right, man.

13:27.890 --> 13:28.599
I'll buy you <i>one.</i>

13:29.851 --> 13:32.478
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

13:32.478 --> 13:34.605
Fiona: <i>Hi, Ray.</i>
<i>Can you give me some advice?</i>

13:34.605 --> 13:36.107
<i>No.</i>

13:36.107 --> 13:38.359
<i>Just kidding.</i>
<i>Yes.</i>

13:38.359 --> 13:39.944
<i>I should've</i>
<i>told you this ‐‐</i>

13:39.944 --> 13:41.946
<i>I'm still</i> technically
<i>with my boyfriend,</i>

13:41.946 --> 13:44.323
<i>even though I only</i>
<i>have feelings for you.</i>

13:44.323 --> 13:45.742
Wow.

13:45.742 --> 13:47.535
I'm the other man.

13:47.535 --> 13:49.078
Like father,
like son.

13:49.078 --> 13:51.873
<i>What's the best way</i>
<i>to break up with my boyfriend</i>

13:51.873 --> 13:53.249
<i>so I don't hurt him?</i>

13:53.249 --> 13:55.376
<i>Tell him</i>
<i>you're moving away.</i>

13:55.376 --> 13:57.628
<i>That would</i>
<i>let him down easy.</i>

13:57.628 --> 13:59.130
<i>Thank you so much.</i>

13:59.130 --> 14:01.007
<i>Can I tell you</i>
<i>one other thing, Ray?</i>

14:01.007 --> 14:01.799
<i>Of course.</i>

14:01.799 --> 14:02.925
<i>I'm moving away.</i>

14:02.925 --> 14:04.260
<i>Oh, no!</i>
<i>Where?</i>

14:04.260 --> 14:06.179
<i>Canada.</i>
<i>I have to leave tonight.</i>

14:06.179 --> 14:07.930
<i>Maybe you can still make</i>
<i>the dance.</i>

14:07.930 --> 14:09.265
<i>What time</i>
<i>is your flight?</i>

14:09.265 --> 14:10.058
<i>What time</i>
<i>in the dance?</i>

14:10.058 --> 14:11.434
<i>‐8:00.</i>
<i>‐7:00.</i>

14:11.434 --> 14:12.685
Damn it!

14:12.685 --> 14:15.104
<i>You'll be okay,</i>
<i>right, Ray?</i>

14:15.104 --> 14:16.564
<i>There's plenty</i>
<i>of fish in the sea.</i>

14:16.564 --> 14:18.733
[ Flatly ]
<i>Yes, of course.</i>

14:18.733 --> 14:20.735
<i>Grabbing my fishing pole</i>
<i>as we speak.</i>

14:20.735 --> 14:21.903
<i>Ha‐ha.</i>

14:21.903 --> 14:22.737
<i>Goodbye, Fiona.</i>

14:22.737 --> 14:25.490
[ Sighs ]

14:27.450 --> 14:30.703
[ Muffled sobbing ]

14:35.208 --> 14:37.168
Uh...

14:37.168 --> 14:38.377
It was me.

14:38.377 --> 14:39.837
What?

14:39.837 --> 14:44.342
Fiona isn't real.

14:44.342 --> 14:47.053
It was just a prank
I was pulling on you.

14:47.053 --> 14:48.262
I don't believe you.

14:48.262 --> 14:51.015
[ Sighs ]
Okay.

14:54.936 --> 14:56.312
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

14:56.312 --> 14:58.022
Fiona:
<i>Do you believe me now?</i>

14:58.022 --> 14:59.607
You monster!

14:59.607 --> 15:02.819
You used me for
your Valentine's Day jollies!

15:02.819 --> 15:05.905
I will never
love again!

15:05.905 --> 15:07.031
Ray.

15:07.031 --> 15:08.783
[ Door opens, closes ]

15:08.783 --> 15:10.159
[ Sighs ]

15:10.159 --> 15:12.120
<i>[ Dance music plays ]</i>
[ Laughter ]

15:12.120 --> 15:13.621
Dr. Miller:
Hey, DiMeos.

15:13.621 --> 15:15.873
How's your
Valentine's Day going?

15:15.873 --> 15:17.291
Not great.

15:17.291 --> 15:18.960
You ruined
my wife's romantic plans

15:18.960 --> 15:20.336
by making us
chaperone.

15:20.336 --> 15:21.671
Maya:
No use dwelling on it.

15:21.671 --> 15:24.132
I mean, I had a lot of heat
planned for tonight,

15:24.132 --> 15:26.551
but it's ruined,
can't be replicated...ever.

15:26.551 --> 15:27.969
Her fault.

15:27.969 --> 15:29.679
Well, yes,
you said that,

15:29.679 --> 15:32.473
but I'm sorry,
you were needed.

15:32.473 --> 15:34.642
You made her
make us come here.

15:34.642 --> 15:37.061
Mnh‐mnh.
Mm‐hmm.

15:37.061 --> 15:38.729
Oh, uh, what's that?
[ Laughs nervously ]

15:40.565 --> 15:43.151
Darling, I'm sorry.
I had something planned for you.

15:43.151 --> 15:44.819
I did,
and I came this close.

15:44.819 --> 15:46.988
I couldn't pull it off.

15:46.988 --> 15:48.156
I had to destroy
Valentine's Day.

15:49.740 --> 15:53.953
Well, that is the most
romantic destructive thing

15:53.953 --> 15:55.037
anyone's ever done
for me.

15:55.037 --> 15:57.373
Is it?
Is it okay?

15:57.373 --> 15:59.959
I mean, even though
we don't have the heat?

15:59.959 --> 16:01.127
We have heat.

16:01.127 --> 16:03.087
We have a different kind
of heat.

16:03.087 --> 16:06.591
Maybe it isn't "break up
an engagement and punch
a guy in the face" heat,

16:06.591 --> 16:10.845
but we've traded up for
"18 years of marriage" heat.

16:10.845 --> 16:13.639
"Beautiful,
perfect family" heat.

16:13.639 --> 16:15.433
Those are good.
Those are heats.

16:15.433 --> 16:17.018
It's a nice,
lived‐in heat.

16:17.018 --> 16:18.853
Hey, you want
to get me a gift?

16:18.853 --> 16:21.564
Don't question <i>us</i> ever.

16:21.564 --> 16:22.940
Okay, well,
the price is right.

16:22.940 --> 16:24.817
All right.
[ Chuckles ]

16:27.904 --> 16:28.905
[ Cellphone chimes ]
Ooh!

16:30.156 --> 16:31.741
Ooh, forget
not questioning us.

16:31.741 --> 16:33.784
I've got
a much better gift for you.

16:33.784 --> 16:35.077
Did he talk to you?

16:35.077 --> 16:37.121
<i>♪ Save me, somehow ♪</i>

16:37.121 --> 16:40.416
<i>♪ One step,</i>
<i>and I'm going down ♪</i>

16:40.416 --> 16:41.500
Ray, come on.

16:41.500 --> 16:43.586
What do I have to do
to make this right?

16:43.586 --> 16:45.796
I'm more mad at myself,

16:45.796 --> 16:47.715
for thinking
I could ever be loved.

16:47.715 --> 16:49.717
So you got catfished
by your kid sister.

16:49.717 --> 16:51.260
Look at the upside ‐‐

16:51.260 --> 16:53.221
now you've got some experience
under your belt.

16:53.221 --> 16:54.430
And you're good at this.

16:54.430 --> 16:56.224
You're ready
for a real girl now.

16:58.351 --> 16:59.477
You're right.

16:59.477 --> 17:01.896
♪♪

17:06.567 --> 17:08.110
I'll go
in a couple minutes.

17:08.110 --> 17:09.654
<i>[ Dance music playing ]</i>
Hey!

17:09.654 --> 17:11.781
Here you go.
Better late than never.

17:11.781 --> 17:13.115
Ohh!
[ Chuckles ]

17:13.115 --> 17:16.160
All right.
Dang.

17:16.160 --> 17:18.454
People sure like
getting candy.

17:18.454 --> 17:21.165
What's so exciting
about a box of chocolates?

17:21.165 --> 17:23.251
Yeah, sure,
there's the mystery.

17:23.251 --> 17:25.086
You know, could be
a creamy center,

17:25.086 --> 17:28.130
could be...nougat.

17:28.130 --> 17:30.383
C‐O ‐‐ "Coconut"?

17:30.383 --> 17:32.552
You never mentioned anything
about coconut.

17:32.552 --> 17:36.055
Is there, like,
one in every box?

17:36.055 --> 17:37.890
Uh, well...
[ Chuckles ]

17:37.890 --> 17:39.725
You deserve a treat.

17:39.725 --> 17:42.520
You've been strong
for the better part of an hour.

17:42.520 --> 17:44.689
♪♪

17:47.483 --> 17:48.818
Damn it, JJ.

17:48.818 --> 17:51.028
I can't believe
you talked me into that.

17:51.028 --> 17:52.405
We are so screwed.

17:52.405 --> 17:54.073
People are gonna
be so mad at us.

17:56.075 --> 17:58.452
Split the last one?

17:58.452 --> 17:59.412
[ Laughter ]

17:59.412 --> 18:01.581
Girl: That is so fun!

18:04.250 --> 18:06.210
How did you do that?

18:09.505 --> 18:11.841
Hi, I'm Ray.

18:11.841 --> 18:13.259
You look ravishing
in that dress.

18:13.259 --> 18:14.635
Why, thank you.

18:14.635 --> 18:15.595
I'm Veronica.

18:15.595 --> 18:17.388
Would you like to dance,
Veronica?

18:17.388 --> 18:20.808
Oh, no, thanks.
I'm not interested.

18:20.808 --> 18:22.310
I'm sorry,
are you insane?

18:22.310 --> 18:23.811
Who are you?

18:23.811 --> 18:25.688
I'm his sister ‐‐
and a new fan.

18:25.688 --> 18:28.941
A couple of days ago, I didn't
know why anyone would like him,

18:28.941 --> 18:30.568
but now I don't know
why anyone wouldn't.

18:30.568 --> 18:32.695
I'm just not really
looking for anything right now.

18:32.695 --> 18:33.821
Well, too bad.

18:33.821 --> 18:35.156
You found something.
Now dance.

18:35.156 --> 18:36.324
Okay, okay.

18:36.324 --> 18:38.826
Forget experience,
Ray.

18:38.826 --> 18:39.994
This is the upside.

18:39.994 --> 18:42.121
You've convinced your sister
that you're a catch,

18:42.121 --> 18:44.040
and your sister
gets things done.

18:44.040 --> 18:46.083
Veronica's gonna
give you a chance.

18:46.083 --> 18:47.460
You're gonna dance,
right, sweetie?

18:47.460 --> 18:48.127
Mm‐hmm.

18:48.127 --> 18:49.170
Thanks?

18:50.421 --> 18:52.632
<i>♪ Oh, yes,</i>
<i>I'll spoil ya ♪</i>

18:52.632 --> 18:54.383
<i>♪ Telling you right now ♪</i>

18:54.383 --> 18:57.053
<i>♪ Oh, yes,</i>
<i>I'll spoil you ♪</i>

18:57.053 --> 18:58.179
[ Whispering ]
It's going great.

18:58.179 --> 19:00.848
[ Sighs ]
You came.

19:00.848 --> 19:03.351
Thank you so much
for changing your mind.

19:03.351 --> 19:04.810
[ Chuckles ]
I didn't do this for you.

19:04.810 --> 19:06.395
I did this for my wife.

19:06.395 --> 19:09.065
She wanted me to close this
chapter in my life and move on,

19:09.065 --> 19:10.399
so I'm gonna
tell you everything

19:10.399 --> 19:12.401
that I remember
about that night.

19:12.401 --> 19:13.444
The bar was McEvoy's.

19:13.444 --> 19:15.696
McEvoy's!
Ooh, I could kiss you!

19:15.696 --> 19:17.406
Where, right here?

19:17.406 --> 19:18.783
You were eating
potato skins.

19:18.783 --> 19:20.743
Oh, that's right!
I was!

19:20.743 --> 19:22.620
And you were wearing
this jacket ‐‐ you left it.

19:22.620 --> 19:24.580
My jacket.

19:24.580 --> 19:26.624
Wait, you saved this?

19:26.624 --> 19:27.833
No.

19:27.833 --> 19:29.835
It was in a box
in the back of my closet.

19:29.835 --> 19:31.379
I was gonna give it
to Allison.

19:31.379 --> 19:33.089
Yeah, it was
a few sizes too big.

19:33.089 --> 19:34.715
Meow!

19:34.715 --> 19:36.217
I almost like you.

19:36.217 --> 19:38.094
Ooh, what was the song
that was playing?

19:38.094 --> 19:39.512
Check your pocket.

19:39.512 --> 19:41.263
Right ‐‐ go have fun.

19:41.263 --> 19:42.723
Re‐create
your special night.

19:42.723 --> 19:43.724
Thank you, Ethan.

19:43.724 --> 19:46.227
I know
this wasn't easy for you.

19:46.227 --> 19:48.604
<i>♪ ...all right,</i>
<i>just one dance ♪</i>

19:48.604 --> 19:53.317
<i>♪ And you kissed me,</i>
<i>and we both knew ♪</i>

19:53.317 --> 19:54.819
Ethan!

19:54.819 --> 19:57.196
What the hell do you think
you're doing?
Hey, man.

19:57.196 --> 19:58.572
[ Crowd gasps ]
Oh, hi.

19:58.572 --> 20:00.991
Really?
There are other women
in the world

20:00.991 --> 20:03.452
who have dark,
curly hair, man.

20:03.452 --> 20:04.870
Oh, my God,
that was so bloody hot.

20:04.870 --> 20:05.913
Was it?
That was heat!

20:05.913 --> 20:07.665
That was heat ‐‐
and the real kind.

20:07.665 --> 20:10.334
Not the sad heat we were
pretending was okay before.

20:10.334 --> 20:11.794
No, screw that heat.

20:11.794 --> 20:13.087
Oi, did you see that?

20:13.087 --> 20:14.088
Yeah.

20:14.088 --> 20:15.047
Hot‐cha.

20:15.047 --> 20:17.508
"I'm gonna puke."

20:17.508 --> 20:19.260
Yeah, we're full
of chocolate and coconut.

20:19.260 --> 20:21.220
<i>♪ And if I start a commotion ♪</i>

20:21.220 --> 20:24.473
<i>♪ I run the risk</i>
<i>of losing you ♪</i>
It's our night, darling.

20:24.473 --> 20:26.100
Shall we dance?
Mm.

20:27.101 --> 20:28.477
Oh, God,
he looks pretty mad.

20:28.477 --> 20:29.687
Shall we run?

20:29.687 --> 20:31.981
♪ Ever fallen in love
with someone? ♪

20:31.981 --> 20:33.149
♪ Ever fallen in love? ♪

20:33.149 --> 20:34.692
♪ In love with someone ♪

20:34.692 --> 20:36.068
♪ Ever fallen in love? ♪

20:36.068 --> 20:37.445
♪ In love with someone ♪

20:37.445 --> 20:39.113
♪ You shouldn't have
fallen in love with ♪

20:42.783 --> 20:45.995
<i>Abra‐kabarba,</i>
<i>alakazaam, ba‐bam.</i>

20:45.995 --> 20:47.955
This is such
a sweet gift.

20:47.955 --> 20:52.334
Mom, you were engaged
to <i>another guy, too?</i>

20:52.334 --> 20:53.794
No, that's your father.

20:53.794 --> 20:54.712
This is what
you've done to me.

20:54.712 --> 20:57.173
Oh, Jimmy, I love it.

20:57.173 --> 20:58.466
It's not done.

20:58.466 --> 20:59.884
I also did the future.

20:59.884 --> 21:01.552
♪♪

21:01.552 --> 21:03.637
Why is everyone aging
but Mom?

21:03.637 --> 21:07.141
'Cause your father
is the most romantic man alive.

21:07.141 --> 21:09.977
Happy Valentine's Day,
darling.

21:09.977 --> 21:12.146
Wait...

21:12.146 --> 21:13.564
I'm not in that one.

21:15.191 --> 21:16.150
Do I die?
